{
 "name": "RPlog_Simon_Sezirok_Meets_Markus_Lisardis",
 "title": "Simon Sezirok Meets Markus Lisardis",
 "summary": "In the bustling Coronet City spaceport, the lost Telgossian wanderer Simon Sezirok keeps a hunter's watch over the crowd, sensing that his waiting is at an end as two YT-1300s arrive. The cold huntress Kacela snatches a flyer and trades a wary stare with Simon before departing, while the Corellian freelancer Markus Lisardis disembarks with his ratty-cloaked young charge Mira, whom he has taken under his wing. Simon greets the pair, and he and Markus fall into a long, searching conversation about home, exile, and family: Simon explains he is forever lost from his land-bound people of Telgosse, while Markus recounts leaving Corellia and his father's capture by the Imperials. Recognizing a noble kinship, Markus introduces himself and Mira and offers Simon his help, the two parting as new acquaintances as the spacer Morrison looks on.",
